# Personal Portfolio

This repository contains the source code for my personal portfolio website. The portfolio showcases my projects, skills, and experience as a developer, while this README will guide you on how to set it up locally and explore the technology behind it.

## Table of Contents
- [Overview](#overview)
- [Tech Stack](#tech-stack)
- [Setup Instructions](#setup-instructions)
- [Features](#features)
- [Contributing](#contributing)
- [License](#license)

## Overview
This project is my personal portfolio website where I showcase my personal code projects. The portfolio is built with modern web technologies, aiming to create a clean, responsive, and interactive experience for visitors.

## Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: HTML, CSS, JavaScript
- **Backend**: Node.js, API integration
- **Databese**: MongoDB, Mongoose
- **Deployment**: Heroku
- **CI/CD**: Github Actions
- **Tools**: GSAP, Webpack
- **Architecture**: MVC

## Features
- **Responsive Design**: Works seamlessly across various devices and screen sizes.
- **Project Showcase**: Detailed project sections with descriptions and live demos.
- **Internationalization (i18n)**: Multi-language support for English and French.
- **Theme Switcher**: Light and dark mode theme switcher.
- **Contact Form**: Integrated form allowing visitors to reach out easily.